parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "WAM",
"software": [
"compilers/intel/2019.4.243",
"intelmpi/2019.4.243",
"netcdf"
],
"resources": [
"nodes: 1",
"tasks per node: 1",
"time: 00:05:00",
"partition: pCluster",
"account: cluster",
"output: ptime_s.o%j",
"error: ptime_s.e%j"
],
"directories": [
"/gpfs/home/ricker/WAM/WAM_Cycle7_test",
"/gpfs/work/ricker/storage/WAM/WAM_Cycle7_test/tempsg"
],
"files": [
"Time_User_S",
"ptime_S",
"ptime_S.exe",
"Time_Prot_S"
]
}
```

This script is running a post-processing step for a WAM (Wave Model) simulation. It uses Intel compilers and MPI library, NetCDF library, and requires one node with one task per node. The script runs for a maximum of 5 minutes and writes output and error files to the specified locations. It also copies necessary files from the WAM directory to a working directory and executes the ptime_S executable, which presumably creates and saves grid files. Finally, the script cleans up by moving the output file and removing the temporary files.
